    <h1>Essays</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Francis Bacon &middot; 1597&ndash;1625 &middot; <a href="https://archive.org/details/essaysoffrancisb00baco">full text (Internet Archive, public domain)</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Cicero built sentences like cathedrals &mdash; subordinate clause nested inside subordinate clause, the meaning suspended until the final verb. Bacon burned the cathedral. His essays are aphorisms: one sentence, one idea, maximum compression. &ldquo;Reading maketh a full man; conference a ready man; and writing an exact man.&rdquo; Three clauses, three facts, no decoration.</p>
    </div>

